  "prompt": "Can I do SEO for AngularJS based sites?",
  "response": "Yes, you can do SEO for AngularJS-based sites, but it requires some specific approaches due to the single-page application (SPA) nature of AngularJS. Here are several strategies:\n\n1. Server-Side Rendering (SSR)\n- Use Angular Universal\n- Implement pre-rendering\n- Use services like Rendertron\n- Use tools like Prerender.io\n\n2. Specific SEO Techniques\n- Use HTML5 mode for clean URLs\n- Implement proper meta tags dynamically\n- Use route resolvers to populate metadata\n- Utilize angular-seo libraries\n\n3. Technical Approaches\n```javascript\n// Example meta tag dynamic update\n$rootScope.$on('$routeChangeSuccess', function(event, current, previous) {\n  $rootScope.title = current.$$route.title;\n  $rootScope.metaDescription = current.$$route.metaDescription;\n});\n```\n\n4. Google Recommendations\n- Use hashbang (#!) for crawlability\n- Implement proper sitemap\n- Use structured data markup\n- Ensure content is crawlable\n\n5. Tools and Frameworks\n- Angular Universal\n- Prerender.io\n- Angular SEO libraries\n- Google Search Console\n\nBest practices include server-side rendering and ensuring search engine-friendly content delivery.",
